id: pm-h85e
title: "GH-471: pm context includes an installed package/extension health summary"
description: "Dogfood GH-471: pm context shows item counts but nothing about extension/package health, forcing separate doctor/health invocations to understand project state. Duplicate check: searched context extension health summary — pm-ishm (GH-445) covers context tag noise only, no overlap."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 3
tags[5]: agent-experience,"area:cli",context,extensions,gh-issue
created_at: "2026-07-06T21:09:04.826Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-14T17:05:08.005Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: pm context output includes a brief installed-packages line with health status (ok/degraded per package); stays token-lean and can be suppressed via a flag or --fields; covered by specs
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: low
confidence: medium
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-tu71,related,"2026-07-14T17:05:07.982Z",null,null
body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/471\n\nAdd a brief installed package/extension health summary to `pm context` so agents can diagnose extension-related issues without separate `pm package doctor` runs. Must respect the context token budget (see GH-445 tag-folding work pm-ishm) — summary line(s), not full diagnostics; opt-out via flag/--fields."
